messages.message: I can do a competitive analysis on terminology. It dovetails nicely with some other terminology work I'm tackling. I'll create a ticket and follow up about scope and resources there.

BTW, in some other thread, I saw someone (in Sales? Support?) calling this "List of objects," which I do think adds some clarity and mostly resolves my expectation that I'm extracting or outputting an actual list.

to summarize what we discussed on Wednesday
• if the data type is “List” and the field has no attributes (screenshot 1)
    ◦ the underlying type is “List”
    ◦ the extracted value is a list of strings
    ◦ the extracted value is shown as a single-column table
• if the data type is “List” and the field has attributes (screenshot 2)
    ◦ the underlying type is “List of objects”
    ◦ the extracted value is a list of objects with the specified attributes
    ◦ the extracted value is shown as a table with each row representing an object and each column representing an attribute
